data.title: WaPo 2307
data.meta_description: WaPo_2307 - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. The document discusses how the ongoing Hollywood strike by writers and actors could supercharge the creator economy by driving more people to create and share content on social networks. As film and TV production halts, online influencers and video makers who attract millions of fans without major industry resources could see rising popularity and cultural influence. The strike may also further blur the lines between traditional and digital forms of fame.
